						<summary>

						<p>Slab paved in the Mukha-maṇḍapa of the Pushpēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Viḷambi, chaitra ba. 3.</hi> However, on the basis of palaeography this may be assigned to the 18th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>It states that Basi Reḍḍi, son of Miṭṭa Pāpi-Reḍḍi worshipped and paid obeisance to god Pushpanātha.</p>						

						</summary>
